                    Video has become one of the most common sources of visual information. But, 
                    as the amount of video data is daunting and the number of videos is rapidly 
                    increasing â€” 72 Hours of video are uploaded to YouTube every 60 seconds 
                    and it takes over 82 years to watch all videos uploaded to YouTube per day! 
                    we need a tool to summarize videos. A tool that aims to compactly depict 
                    the original video to make a shorter watchable video with the important events 
                    presented in a shorter period of time. 
          
                    In our project, we implemented one of the ways of video summarization 
                    using Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) to model the variable-range 
                    temporal dependency among video frames, 
                    so as to derive both representative and compact video summaries.
